Magnum Mining & Exploration Ltd – Quarterly Report Summary (30 June 2025)

Capital Raising

  • Renounceable Entitlement Offer:
  • Successfully raised $0.5M (AUD) (26 June 2025) at $0.002/share.
  • Shortfall Offer: 876.6M shares remaining for potential issuance.
  • Prior $1.9M Non-Renounceable Entitlement Offer voided (28 May 2025) due to failing minimum subscription ($0.5M).

Acquisitions & Projects

  • USA Copper-Gold Projects:
  • Parker Project: Surface samples up to 83.87 g/t Au, 8.37% Cu, 359 g/t Ag.
  • Mormon Canyon Project: Historic drill grades up to 3.32 g/t Au, 4.72% Cu.
  • Brazil Rare Earths: Completed acquisition of Palmares (5 May 2025), with trench samples up to 1.69% TREO.

Financials (Appendix 5B)

  • Cash Balance: $1.04M (end quarter).
  • Net Cash Used in Operations: ($0.29M).
  • Exploration Spend: $55,320 (quarter).

Key Dates

  • Entitlement Offer Close: 24 June 2025 (completed).

No further material information identified.

• Exploration Update: Completion of 941m SLRC drill program at Salt Creek Project (NE of Kalgoorlie).

  • Project Scale: 223km² in Goldfields region, prospective for gold, copper, and nickel.
  • Next Steps: Data to guide further exploration; no assay results disclosed.

Material Information Summary:

  • Drilling Results:
  • 9,538m of new drilling completed at Lac Carheil, adding 4,995m of graphitic carbon intervals (~595% increase from prior drilling).

  • 52% of drilled meters yielded graphite intercepts.

  • New SE Extension Zone:

  • 2,777m of graphite intercepts confirmed, with a weighted mean grade of 12.4% TGC.

  • 72% of intercepts exceed the current MRE average grade of 11.5% TGC.

  • Original SE Resource Zone:

  • 1,508m of new graphite intercepts added, with a weighted mean grade of 11.9% TGC.

  • Connector Zone:

  • 710m of graphite intercepts confirmed, linking SE and NW zones, with 9.0% TGC average grade.

  • Next Steps:

  • Mineral Resource Estimate (MRE) update expected this quarter.

  • Mining consultant (DRA Americas) appointed to advance Pre-Feasibility Study (PFS), including mine planning and infrastructure design.

  • Grant Funding:

  • ~A$660k awarded by Quebec government for R&D related to graphite processing.

No capital raising, trading halt, or financial figures (e.g., cash balance) disclosed.

Material Information Summary (Quarterly Report - Appendix 4C)

Operational Highlights:

  • Copper production: 2,593 tonnes (down 12.2% QoQ), grade 0.77% Cu (vs. 0.99% prior quarter).
  • Tonnes processed: 353kt (+11.7% QoQ) with improved recoveries (95.2% vs. 94.2%).
  • Nugent development accelerated: First ore mined ahead of schedule; targets 1.7–1.8Mtpa throughput by H1 2026.
  • Mine development: 2,011 metres (+10.7% QoQ), but lower stope grades (0.78% vs. 0.96%).

Financial Highlights:

  • Operating cashflow: $6.4M (mine-level), net cashflow -$4.8M (incl. $5.1M Nugent capex).
  • C1 cost: $5.24/lb (up from $4.19/lb), All-in cost: US$4.44/lb (vs. $3.79/lb), but FY guidance maintained at US$3.40–3.90/lb (ex-Nugent).
  • Realized copper price: A$14,340/t (up from A$14,137/t).

Liquidity & Capital:

  • Cash & receivables: $24.0M (vs. $20.9M prior quarter).
  • Capital raising completed: Tranche 2 Placement + SPP added $7.6M in liquidity.
  • Hedging: 5,950t copper at A$14,272/t avg. (Jul 2025–Sep 2026).

Exploration:

  • Significant drill results:
  • Nugent: 26m @ 1.21% Cu, 0.27g/t Au.
  • Kavanagh: 13m @ 2.24% Cu.
  • Resource update expected Q4 2025.

Outlook:

  • Production guidance revised to lower end of 12,000–14,000t Cu for 2025.
  • Costs expected to decline post-Nugent contractor demobilization (Q3).
